  "lyrics": "In your purple sky, yeah, I can see you flyin', in your purple sky, you're dyin', you're haulin' it all up, and so on. Can't you feel it a little bit, when you do the things you do? Can't you feel it just a little bit, when you do the things you do? Rainin' on my mind, you're rainin' on everything inside, the divine dividing us here. Do you see what you do, in your reflection of the way you feel? In your purple sky, purple sky, through all the black blue nights, all you'll see is your purple light. World to you, world to you, and parts to me, and parts to you, and parts to me. World to you, world to you, but to see is disorder hereditary. Is it scary up here? You can't feel me at all. Ooh, how long will you feel it at all? And will you heed the ozone in your mind long, and I don't know if you see me there, fading away between the blues and royalty, I'm fading away in this travesty. And will you heed the ozone in your mind long, and I don't know if you see me there, fading away between the blues and royalty, I'm fading away in this travesty Can't, can't, can't find me now, comin' up. Can't, can't, can't find me now, comin' up. Can't, can't, can't call me now, comin' up. Can't, can't find me now, comin' up. Can't, can't find me now, comin' up. Can't, can't, can't find me now, comin' up. For your air and your sky, I know you wanna be free. Where did your bonhomie disease take y'all?",
